#### E. Cancelling the offset - II

A minor drawback of these current source circuits is the need for a base voltage offset by $V_{\mathrm{BE}} \approx$ 0.6 V from the voltage desired across the emitter resistor, which sets the output current. This is similar to the offset issue in an emitter follower, and the same trick (2.2.5D) can be used for approximate cancellation in problematic situations.

